<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Using a bad AT27C080 for UNROM repro]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10327&amp;p=115750#p115750"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">FARID wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Do you think it works?<br /></div><br />Should work, if you can find 3 bytes of free ZP RAM and enough ROM to initialize those 3 bytes (and the game doesn't wipe them at any point, and the IRQ handler isn't sensitive to timing modifications!)... But I'll go out on a limb here and guess that most UNROM games don't use IRQ at all, so you should probably just try the game(s) and see what happens.<br /><br />Better yet, open it/them in FCEUX or another emulator with a decent CPU debugger and look up the address specified in the IRQ vector, to see if the code there looks like an IRQ handler at all. If you're not sure, you can set up an execution breakpoint for that address and see when/whether it runs and returns with an RTI.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sat Jul 27, 2013 12:56 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
