<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Using a bad AT27C080 for UNROM repro]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10327&amp;p=115749#p115749"><![CDATA[
If that RAM isn't used, and you have some ROM space to make it program the RAM, and it doesn't need precisely the timing, then it might work.<br /><br />(Note: BRK instruction is another way to IRQ. Also, if the program reads the IRQ vector for any other reason, that can also mess it up. The expansion port can also trigger IRQ, but as far as I know this was never used.)<br /><br />(And, like it is said, many UNROM games may not use the IRQ anyways.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4734">zzo38</a> — Sat Jul 27, 2013 12:51 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
