<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Using a bad AT27C080 for UNROM repro]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10327&amp;p=115744#p115744"><![CDATA[
Like lidnariq said, mappers aren't the only source of IRQs. Even an NROM game can use IRQs generated by the sound hardware inside the NES. I don't think many UNROM games do it though. If they don't use DMC samples, it may be reasonably safe to assume they don't use IRQs.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sat Jul 27, 2013 11:48 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
