I have an unused AT27C080 EPROM which is a little bad for some unknown reason, Its last offset is 00 instead of being FF<br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/IRQ" class="postlink">As I know the last two offsets of the CPU ($FFFE and $FFFF) are for IRQ</a><br /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/UNROM" class="postlink">On the other hand it seems that UNROM don't have any IRQ</a><br />So I want to know whether I can use this AT27C080 for UNROM repro safely or not?<br />Thanks in advance<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4330">FARID</a> — Sat Jul 27, 2013 6:12 am</p><hr />
